{"word":"φυλακτέος","slug":"φυλακτέος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>φυλακτέος</b></el> <el>(φυλακτέος, η, ον,) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:verbal Adjective'>verb. <a href='S:Adjective'>adj.</a></a> of <a href='S:φυλάσσω'><el>φυλάσσω</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to be watched</i> or <i>kept</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><el>φυλακτέον</el> <i>one must observe, obey</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>(from <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a>) <i>one must guard against</i>, <el>τι</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}